Package ru.tinkoff.qa.neptune.core.api.event.firing.annotations

Annotation Type CaptureOnSuccess

  • @Retention(RUNTIME)
@Target({TYPE,FIELD})
public @interface CaptureOnSuccess
    Annotates subclasses of SequentialGetStepSupplier and SequentialActionSupplier to define which capture should be made then step is succeed. All parameters defined by this annotation are inherited by subclasses. Also it may be overridden in subclasses by declaration of another CaptureOnSuccess. Also it annotates fields subclasses of SequentialGetStepSupplier and SequentialActionSupplier. Values of annotated fields form captures then step is succeed.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element Description
      java.lang.Class<? extends Captor>[] by  

    • Element Detail

      • by

        java.lang.Class<? extends Captor>[] by
        Returns:
        subclasses of Captor that make captures on success. ATTENTION!!! Defined classes should have no declared constructors or they should have declared constructors without parameters. Also, it is possible to define abstract classes there, but if they have no non-abstract subclasses in classpath then they are ignored
